  "prompt": "What is the best quiz question asked ever?",
  "response": "The \"best\" quiz question can vary greatly depending on context, audience, and purpose. However, a classic example that often engages people and prompts interesting discussion is:\n\n**\"What is the one thing you can never have more of, no matter how much money you make?\"**\n\nThis question encourages critical thinking and can lead to various interpretations, with the most common answer being \"time.\" It highlights the value of time and can spark deeper conversations about priorities, life choices, and personal values. \n\nUltimately, the effectiveness of a quiz question depends on how well it resonates with the audience and encourages participation or reflection.",
